suncertify.util

Class Utils

  • java.lang.Object
    • suncertify.util.Utils

  • public final class Utils
extends Object
    Utils contains a collection of useful helper methods that are common to different parts of the application or have very reusable logic, such as methods for converting data types to another type.

      • writeString

        public static void writeString(RandomAccessFile raf,
                               String fieldValue,
                               int fieldSize)
                        throws IOException
        Converts the specified fieldValue String into a byte[] and uses the specified raf to write the value to its file. If the length of the byte[] is less than the specified fieldSize, the remaining bytes are filled with blank spaces.
        Parameters:
        raf - a RandomAccessFile object for reading and writing to a file.
        fieldValue - the field value
        fieldSize - the maximum number of bytes the field should take up in the database.
        Throws:
        IOException - Signals that an I/O exception has occurred.
